  <div class="post-content" itemprop="articleBody">
    <p>It feels uncomfortable for me to write this, since itâ€™s not exactly good news, but here goes: I need to take some time away from this site.</p>
<p><a href="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/0642b-polaovenfacadetile1.jpg"><img decoding="async" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5337342588699078274" class="alignnone" src="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/0642b-polaovenfacadetile1.jpg?w=298" alt="" width="1190" height="1200" border="0" /></a><br />
As youâ€™ve probably noticed, Iâ€™ve been struggling a bit here in recent weeks, trying to keep this blog sailing along at her usual clip, and itâ€™s not working very well. Between helping Brandon with <a href="http://orangette.blogspot.com/2008/11/i-cant-wait.html">Delancey</a> and meeting my own work deadlines, Iâ€™ve been stretched thin. Iâ€™m not doing a very good job of any of it. Actually, Iâ€™m doing a pretty awful job of all of it.</p>
<p><a href="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3056c-425300021.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5337349169149695570" class="alignnone" src="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/3056c-425300021.jpg?w=300" alt="" width="1600" height="1061" border="0" /></a><br />
This site has always been about a kind of love &#8211; a love for food, namely, and for writing &#8211; but right now, that love is temporarily redirected toward some other, more immediate demands, like helping my husband to tile and grout the (ginormous) facade of a pizza oven. In the spirit of keeping it real around here, I have to admit that I need some time to focus on the restaurant &#8211; and, if weâ€™re being deadly honest, to try to enjoy the process, rather than feel overwhelmed by it. I also have some work-related travel coming up, and it needs my attention, too.</p>
<p><a href="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/2471e-polabrandonovenfacade1.jpg"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" id="BLOGGER_PHOTO_ID_5337346074315367618" class="alignnone" src="http://orangette.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/2471e-polabrandonovenfacade1.jpg?w=247" alt="" width="1034" height="1258" border="0" /></a><br />
Iâ€™ll be back in a few weeks with the well refilled, I hope, and with plenty of recipes and stories for you. In the meantime, I hope youâ€™ll understand my silence. With summer so close, and barbecues and gin and tonics and whatnot, Iâ€™ll bet you wonâ€™t even notice.</p>
