    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, </p>
<p>Have you heard of &#8220;slow blogging&#8221;? It is the same as Slow Food. Slow down! Slow blogging is for those of us who know we don&#8217;t ALWAYS have something snappy to say. We write when the spirit moves us and not because we are meeting someone else&#8217;s deadline. (I&#8217;m a slow blogger.)</p>
<p>SLOW down, enjoy the summer&#8230; and blog when it makes you happy&#8230;and never, ever because you feel like you have to. </p>
<p>Cheers. Have a gin and tonic.</p>
    </div>

